law.text:
The department may issue negotiable bonds in order to raise funds to:
Acquire rights of way or other real or personal property necessary for constructing a bridge or bridge approach;
Pay for the purchase or condemnation of a bridge or bridge approach;
Build or cause to be built any bridge including approaches;
Pay for the preparations of plans, specifications and blueprints, and other expenses incidental to the building or purchase of the bridge or bridge approach; and
Pay the cost of bridge construction, repair, enlargement or reconstruction authorized under KRS 180.105 or KRS 180.106.
